Ask HN: Do you know the accelerator/VC firm Antler?
text:
What was your experience there?

Particularly if you didn’t get funded how did it impact your career? Was it a good use of your time and (lack of) money?

I would be joining as a founder without a startup, which makes the whole thing less “driven”. I mean startups pivot all the time so it’s not these relevant but it worries me slightly to be joining without any clear purpose other than “finding a match”. I guess I should look at it like a free “Master in Startups”.

I’m particularly curious about the network and the opportunity for people who “failed” the first stage and didn’t get founded. Or got funded but burned through the 80k and didn’t manage to raise any more money.

What was life after that? Did you get hired by a fellow cofounder from your cohort? Did you get hired by Antler past companies? Did you wonder the land without a penny to your name?

Multiple Vulnerabilities in MobaXterm
text:
MobaXterm has multiple vulnerabilites, which can lead to man in the middle attcks.

Due to a missing fingerprint check, it's possible to intercept the ssh client. Even publickey authentication can be intercepted because the ssh-agent is forwarded in the default configuration.

An update to the latest version of MobaXterm is strongly recommended.

Full disclosure:

* https://docs.ssh-mitm.at/vulnerabilities/CVE-2022-38336.html

* https://docs.ssh-mitm.at/vulnerabilities/CVE-2022-38337.html
